Feb 27, 2024 10:26:00am
Daniel Adto
File and Storage Services includes technologies that help you set up and manage one or more file servers, which are servers that provide central locations on your network where you can store files and share them here

If your users need access to the same files and applications, or if centralized backup and file management are important to your organization, you should set up one or more servers as a file server by installing the File and Storage Services role and the appropriate role services."


File storage (aka file-based storage or file-level storage) is the type of data storage where data is stored in a hierarchical file and folder structure. A file is stored as a whole without breaking down the data into blocks, such as in block storage.


Examples: G-Drive, Dropbox,Icloud, Onedrive

Whether to install File and Storage Services depends on your needs, administrators can use the File and Storage Services role to set up and manage multiple file servers and their storage capabilities by using Server Manager or Windows PowerShell. Some of the specific applications include the following:

• Storage Spaces - Use to deploy high availability storage that is resilient and scalable by using cost-effective industry-standard disks.

• Folder Redirection, Offline Files, and Roaming User Profiles - Use to redirect the path of local folders (such as the Documents folder) or an entire user profile to a network location, while caching the contents locally for increased speed and availability.

• Work Folders - Use to enable users to store and access work files on personal PCs and devices, in addition to corporate PCs. Users gain a convenient location to store work files and access them from anywhere. Organizations maintain control over corporate data by storing the files on centrally managed file servers and optionally specifying user device policies (such as encryption and lock screen passwords). Work Folders is a new role service in Windows Server 2012 R2.

• Data Deduplication - Use to reduce the disk space requirements of your files, saving money on storage.

• iSCSI Target Server - Use to create centralized, software-based, and hardware-independent iSCSI disk subsystems in storage area networks (SANs).

• Server Manager - Use to remotely manage multiple file servers from a single window.

• Windows PowerShell Use to automate the management of the majority of administration tasks for file servers.

gives life meaning and fulfillment. ⭐

This week, we have 𝐅𝐎𝐔𝐑 amazing events for you to showcase your creativity and skills. 🎨📝

𝗢𝗡-𝗧𝗛𝗘-𝗦𝗣𝗢𝗧 𝗣𝗢𝗦𝗧𝗘𝗥 𝗠𝗔𝗞𝗜𝗡𝗚

DATE : 𝗗𝗘𝗖𝗘𝗠𝗕𝗘𝗥 𝟭𝟰, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟯

Requirements:
📌 1/4 Illustration Board
📌 Oil Pastel
📌 Pencil
📌 Ruler

Mechanics:
- One representative per section
- No phones or other devices allowed
- Theme will be revealed on the day of the event
- Submit one entry only

The following criteria is as follows:
Relevance to the Theme - 40%
Originality - 30%
Visual Appeal - 20%
Technical Execution - 10%

𝗢𝗡-𝗧𝗛𝗘-𝗦𝗣𝗢𝗧 𝗘𝗦𝗦𝗔𝗬 𝗪𝗥𝗜𝗧𝗜𝗡𝗚

DATE : 𝗗𝗘𝗖𝗘𝗠𝗕𝗘𝗥 𝟭𝟰, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟯

Requirements:
📌 Intermediate pad
📌 Pen

Mechanics:
- One representative per section
- No phones or other devices allowed
- Topic will be revealed on the day of the event
- Handwritten essay of 500 words or less
- Submit one entry only

The following criteria is as follows:
Relevance to the Theme - 40%
Content and Organization- 30%
Grammar and Mechanics - 20%
Word Choice and Style - 10%

𝗖𝗔𝗥𝗧𝗘𝗦𝗜𝗔𝗡 𝗔𝗥𝗧 𝗠𝗔𝗞𝗜𝗡𝗚

DEADLINE OF SUBMISSION : 𝗝𝗔𝗡𝗨𝗔𝗥𝗬 𝟯, 𝟭𝟭:𝟱𝟵 𝗣.𝗠

Mechanics:
- One representative per section
- Use graphing software such as Desmos, GeoGebra, or any graphing calculator
- Compile your equations, inequalities, and output into a PDF file
- Screen-record the process of creating the output
- Submit one entry only

The criteria is as follows:
Visual Appeal - 40%
Accuracy and Precision - 30%
Originality - 20%
Complexity - 10%

𝗥𝗨𝗕𝗜𝗞'𝗦 𝗖𝗨𝗕𝗘

DATE : 𝗗𝗘𝗖𝗘𝗠𝗕𝗘𝗥 𝟭𝟰, 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟯

Requirements:
📌 Rubik's Cube

Mechanics:
- At least one representative per section (max: 3)
- Provide your own Rubik's Cube
- Best of 3 format
- Delegate will scramble the cube before each attempt
- In case of issues during an attempt, delegates may grant an extra attempt. Report incidents promptly for assessment.

GENESIS IN REVERSE

In the beginning was the earth.
It was beauuuuutiful and man lived upooooon the earth.
And man said: “Let us build skyscrapers and expressways”.
And man covered the earth with STEEL and CONCRETE.
And man said: “It was good”.

On the second day.
Man look upon the cleeaaar bluee waters of the earth, CLEAR BLUE WATERS OF THE EARTH
And man said: “Let us dump sewage and waste into the water”.
And man did. The waters become dark and murky. Daaaark and murky.
And man said: “It is good”

PAM, PAM, PAM, PAM, PAM, PAM, PAM, PAM
PAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAM
PAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAMPAM

On the third day.
Man gazed at the forest on the earth.
They were taaall and green.
He picked up his axe!!!
And man said: “Let us cut the trees and build things for ourselves!)
And man did.
: I want to grow don't cut me!
:I want to live don't cut me!
:I'll give you fresh air, please don't chop me!
CUT!! CUT!! CUT!! (im dying sabi ng puno) And the forest grew thin.
And man said: “It is good”.

Man gazed at the forest on the earth.
They were taaall and green.
He picked up his axe!!!
And man said: “Let us cut the trees and build things for ourselves!)
And man did.
: NO!! NO!!I want to grow don't cut me!
:NO PLEASE NO!! I want to live don't cut me!
:I'll give you fresh air, please don't chop me, PLEASE!!!HUHU
CUT!! CUT!! CUT!! (im dying sabi ng puno) And the forest grew thin!
WHERE ARE MY EGGS! WHERE ARE MY EGGS!! MY NESTLING, NO MORE PLACE TO STAY!!(OMEYAK)

SOIL EROSIONS!!LANDSLIDES!!
FLOODSSS!!! AHHHHHHHH!!!!!!
And man said: “It is good”.

On the fourth day.
Man saw animals leaping in the fields and playing in the sun.
And man said: “Let us trap the animals for money, money, and more money! I'll be rich..ha..ha..ha
and shoot them for sport!
And man did.*binaril yung tatlo
And animals become scarce, scarce!, scarce!
And man said: “It is good”.

On the fifth day.
Man felt the cool breeze in his nostrils.
And man said: Let us burn our refuse and let the wind blowwww away the smoke and debris.
And man did. And the air becomes dense! with smoke, smoke! and carbon.
Disappearing ozone layer
cough, cough, cough
POLLUTION! POLLUTION! POLLUTION!
And man said: “It is good”.

na na naheya
naheya ha naha
naheya heya na yanuwa
hanahe yunu wa na
On the sixth day.

Man saw many kindssssss of people on the earth.
Different races, color and creed. And man feared and said:
“Let us make bombs and missiles in case misunderstanding arise”.
Please no!! please!!
And man did. And missiles site and bomb dumps checkered the landscape.
Look what you've done!
And man said: “It is good”
May umiiyak.
Please! cry no moree!

Hushhhhhh......Hushhhhh
On the seventh day.
Man rested.
And the earth was quiet and deathly still.
For man was no more.
And it was good.

DARA, DUMDUM, DARA, DUMDUM ETC.

James Keith Doligol
1. To improve the physical health of students. Physical fitness activities help develop cardiovascular endurance, muscular strength, flexibility, and overall physical fitness.
2. To identify any underlying health issues or risk factors that may affect physical fitness, such as high blood pressure or cardiovascular conditions.
3. To evaluate the current physical fitness level of the participants. This helps individuals gain insight into their strengths and weaknesses.
4. To motivate individuals by showing them the benefits of regular physical activity and raising awareness about the importance of fitness for overall health.
5. To help individuals set realistic and achievable fitness goals based on their current fitness level and desired outcomes.
